00:06:17.790 --> 00:06:21.919
Speaking of billionaires, the goods that travelled
on the Silk Road really only changed the lives

00:06:21.919 --> 00:06:27.050
of rich people. Did the Silk Road affect the
rest of us? Yes, for three reasons.

00:06:27.050 --> 00:06:31.780
First, wider economic impact. Relatively few
people could afford silk, but a lot of people

00:06:31.780 --> 00:06:34.100
devoted their lives to making that silk.

00:06:34.100 --> 00:06:38.020
And as the market for silk grew, more and
more people chose to go into silk production

00:06:38.030 --> 00:06:40.340
rather than doing something else with their
lives.

00:06:40.340 --> 00:06:44.930
Second, the Silk Road didn’t just trade
luxury goods. In fact, arguably the most important

00:06:44.930 --> 00:06:47.280
thing traded along the Silk Road: ideas.

00:06:47.280 --> 00:06:51.220
For example, the Silk Road was the primary
route for the spread of Buddhism.When we last

00:06:51.220 --> 00:06:56.020
saw the Buddha’s Eight-Fold Path to escaping
the cycle of suffering and desire that's inherent

00:06:56.020 --> 00:06:59.400
to humans, it was beginning to dwindle in
India.

00:06:59.400 --> 00:07:03.240
But through contacts with other cultures and
traditions, Buddhism grew and flourished and

00:07:03.240 --> 00:07:06.000
became one of the great religious traditions
of the world.

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:10.420
The variation of Buddhism that took root in
China, Korea, Japan, and Central Asia is known

00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:14.169
as Mahayana Buddhism, and it differed from
the original teachings of the Buddha in many

00:07:14.169 --> 00:07:19.650
ways, but one that was fundamental. For Mahayana
Buddhists, the Buddha was divine. (I mean,

00:07:19.650 --> 00:07:24.000
we can—and religious historians do—fight
over the exact definition of divine, but in

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.400
Mahayanna Buddhism, there’s no question
that the Buddha is venerated to a greater degree.

00:07:28.400 --> 00:07:32.600
The idea of Nirvana also transformed from
a release from that cycle of suffering and

00:07:32.600 --> 00:07:37.460
desire to something much more heavenly and
frankly more fun, and in some versions of

00:07:37.460 --> 00:07:42.340
Mahayana Buddhism, there are lots of different
heavens, each more awesome than the last.

00:07:42.340 --> 00:07:45.920
Rather than focusing on the fundamental fact
of suffering, Mahayana Buddhism offered the

00:07:45.930 --> 00:07:50.430
hope that through worship of the Buddha, or
one of the many bodhisattvas – holy people

00:07:50.430 --> 00:07:54.870
who could have achieved nirvana but chose
to hang out on Earth with us because they’re

00:07:54.870 --> 00:07:57.730
super nice– one could attain a good afterlife.

00:07:57.730 --> 00:08:02.000
Many merchants on the silk road became strong
supporters of monasteries which in turn became

00:08:02.010 --> 00:08:04.169
convenient weigh stations for caravans.

00:08:04.169 --> 00:08:08.529
And by endowing the monasteries, rich merchants
were buying a form of supernatural insurance;

00:08:08.529 --> 00:08:11.840
Monks who lived in the monasteries would pray
for the success of trade missions and the

00:08:11.840 --> 00:08:16.680
health of their patrons. It was win-win, especially
when you consider that one of the central

00:08:16.680 --> 00:08:20.280
materials used in Mahayana Buddhist rituals
is … silk.

00:08:20.280 --> 00:08:24.160
And a third reason the silk road changed all
our lives, worldwide interconnectedness of

00:08:24.169 --> 00:08:26.749
populations led to the spread of disease.

00:08:26.749 --> 00:08:31.260
Measles and Smallpox traveled along it, as
did bubonic plague, which came from the East

00:08:31.260 --> 00:08:37.360
to the West in 534, 750, and—most devastatingly—in
1346.

00:08:37.360 --> 00:08:42.119
This last plague—known as the Black Death—resulted
in the largest population decimation in human

00:08:42.119 --> 00:08:46.299
history, with nearly half of Europeans dying
in a four-year period.

00:08:46.300 --> 00:08:50.759
A sizable majority of people living in Italy
died as did two-thirds of Londoners.

00:08:50.759 --> 00:08:54.430
And it quite possibly wouldn’t have happened
without the Silk Road. If you were living

00:08:54.430 --> 00:08:58.959
in London during the fourteenth century, you
probably didn’t blame the Silk Road for

00:08:58.959 --> 00:09:01.720
your community’s devastation, but it played
a role.

00:09:01.720 --> 00:09:06.459
If you look at it that way, the interconnectedness
fostered by Silk Road affected way, way more

00:09:06.459 --> 00:09:11.319
people than just those rich enough to buy
silk, just as today’s globalization offers

00:09:11.319 --> 00:09:14.259
both promise and threat to each of us.

